cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.DS 

This paper is about optimizing ranking measures, which is a common problem in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions collaborative filtering, which falls under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of structured estimation in Hilbert spaces, which is related to optimization problems in computer vision (cs.CV) and data structures (cs.DS).
